Updates for ADIOS v1.5.12

From testing, ADIOS v2.0.0 incurs additional overhead on CPUs with many cores
Continue with ADIOS v1.5.12 + backports (B) at this time

 BOOST file_mapping parallel reads (64 threads)
 rgn.advise(bip::mapped_region::advice_willneed)
 mq-deadline   :  2.200  2.190  2.180  2.165  2.199
 adios 2.0.0   :  3.246  3.491  3.305  3.346  3.498
 adios 1.5.12+ :  2.648  2.560  2.581  2.541  2.543 (A)
 adios 1.5.12+ :  2.380  2.396  2.382  2.369  2.377 (B)

(A) ADIOS v1.5.12 + backports
  - Relax default_global_latency_window (32ms)
  - Increase default_bq_refill_below_ratio (25)
  - Sync default 1m_shrink options (v2.0.0-rc4)
  - Reposition requests unconditionally (v2.0.0-rc3)

(B) ADIOS v1.5.12 + backports
  - Relax default_global_latency_window (37ms)
  - Increase default_bq_refill_below_ratio (23)
  - Sync default 1m_shrink options (v2.0.0-rc4)
  - Reposition requests unconditionally (v2.0.0-rc3)

Signed-off-by: Mario Roy <...>


